</taxonomicName>
combines characters typically observed in 
<taxonomicName id="4C354D76FF89FF94FB09FF06FAE9FF1D" authorityName="Erichson" authorityYear="1839" box="[1274,1379,221,244]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Arpedium" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="65" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B941EAE7FF89FF94FB09FF06FAE9FF1D" box="[1274,1379,221,244]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="65">Arpedium</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
with those of 
<taxonomicName id="4C354D76FF89FF94FF07FEDBFEF1FEFE" authorityName="Reitter" authorityYear="1909" box="[244,379,256,279]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Eucnecosum" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="65" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B941EAE7FF89FF94FF07FEDBFEF1FEFE" box="[244,379,256,279]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="65">Eucnecosum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, thus rendering the separation of these taxa on the generic level doubtful. Based on the absence of microsculpture of the forebody, the long apical palpomere of the maxillary palpus (similar to the condition in 
<taxonomicName id="4C354D76FF89FF94FAC1FEF9FE99FEB5" authority="Fauvel" authorityName="Fauvel" authorityYear="1878" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Arpedium" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="65" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cribratum">
<emphasis id="B941EAE7FF89FF94FAC1FEF9FF35FEB5" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="65">A. cribratum</emphasis>
Fauvel
</taxonomicName>
), the shape of the impressions in front of the ocelli, as well as the rather coarse puncturation of the head and pronotum, the new species would have to be placed in 
<taxonomicName id="4C354D76FF89FF94FD07FEB3FCD7FE96" authorityName="Erichson" authorityYear="1839" box="[756,861,360,383]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Arpedium" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="65" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B941EAE7FF89FF94FD07FEB3FCD7FE96" box="[756,861,360,383]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="65">Arpedium</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, whereas in size, shape and length of the wings, the presence of distinct pubescence on the forebody, and the relatively short antennae it is more similar to species currently attributed to 
<taxonomicName id="4C354D76FF89FF94FEECFE76FE2CFE2D" authorityName="Reitter" authorityYear="1909" box="[287,422,429,452]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Eucnecosum" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="65" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B941EAE7FF89FF94FEECFE76FE2CFE2D" box="[287,422,429,452]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="65">Eucnecosum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Moreover, a comparison of several species of 
<taxonomicName id="4C354D76FF89FF94FC6DFE76FB8DFE2D" authorityName="Erichson" authorityYear="1839" box="[926,1031,429,452]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Arpedium" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="65" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B941EAE7FF89FF94FC6DFE76FB8DFE2D" box="[926,1031,429,452]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="65">Arpedium</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C354D76FF89FF94FBC8FE76FB48FE2D" authorityName="Reitter" authorityYear="1909" box="[1083,1218,429,452]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Eucnecosum" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="65" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B941EAE7FF89FF94FBC8FE76FB48FE2D" box="[1083,1218,429,452]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="65">Eucnecosum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
yielded no convincing evidence that both are distinct on the generic level. The characters indicated in the literature (see introduction) to distinguish the two taxa (e. g. presence/absence of microsculpture, length and density of pubescence, length of antennae, relative length of palpomeres) do not seem to justify such a distinction. Finally, I have been unable to appreciate the presence/absence of a subocular ridge as a useful character. This ridge is more or less pronounced in all 
<taxonomicName id="4C354D76FF89FF94FB38FDE3FABEFDA6" authorityName="Erichson" authorityYear="1839" box="[1227,1332,568,591]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Arpedium" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="65" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B941EAE7FF89FF94FB38FDE3FABEFDA6" box="[1227,1332,568,591]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="65">Arpedium</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C354D76FF89FF94FA99FDE3FEC6FD98" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Eucnecosum" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="65" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="undetermined">
<emphasis id="B941EAE7FF89FF94FA99FDE3FF7EFD98" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="65">Eucnecosum</emphasis>
species
</taxonomicName>
, but can be seen in ventral aspect only in those species with rather large eyes; in species with eyes of reduced size it is usually covered by the (more or less bulging) subocular portion of the head and can be seen only in lateral aspect. In conclusion, there is little doubt that 
<taxonomicName id="4C354D76FF89FF94FD40FD7BFCB0FD5E" authorityName="Reitter" authorityYear="1909" box="[691,826,672,695]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Eucnecosum" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="65" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B941EAE7FF89FF94FD40FD7BFCB0FD5E" box="[691,826,672,695]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="65">Eucnecosum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
will eventually have to be treated as a subgenus again or may even have to be synonymised with 
<taxonomicName id="4C354D76FF89FF94FDB6FD19FD24FD30" authorityName="Erichson" authorityYear="1839" box="[581,686,706,729]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Arpedium" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="65" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B941EAE7FF89FF94FDB6FD19FD24FD30" box="[581,686,706,729]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="65">Arpedium</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Such changes, however, should be based on a thorough phylogenetic study of these taxa, which is not within the scope of the present paper.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B8A36F5FF89FF94FF34FCDCFE86FCA8" blockId="2.[151,1437,151,1423]" pageId="2" pageNumber="65">
<emphasis id="B941EAE7FF89FF94FF34FCDCFE2FFCF6" bold="true" box="[199,421,775,799]" inLineHeading="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="65" reason="1">Comparative notes.</emphasis>
The new species is distinguished from other Palaearctic species of 
<taxonomicName id="4C354D76FF89FF94FB8BFCD3FB6BFCF6" authorityName="Erichson" authorityYear="1839" box="[1144,1249,776,799]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Arpedium" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="65" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B941EAE7FF89FF94FB8BFCD3FB6BFCF6" box="[1144,1249,776,799]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="65">Arpedium</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C354D76FF89FF94FAE6FCD3FA16FCF6" authorityName="Reitter" authorityYear="1909" box="[1301,1436,776,799]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Eucnecosum" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="65" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B941EAE7FF89FF94FAE6FCD3FA16FCF6" box="[1301,1436,776,799]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="65">Eucnecosum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as follows:
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B8A36F5FF89FF94FF34FC96FBF2FBF8" blockId="2.[151,1437,151,1423]" pageId="2" pageNumber="65">
From 
<taxonomicName id="4C354D76FF89FF94FEFBFC96FE0CFC8D" baseAuthorityName="Gravenhorst" baseAuthorityYear="1806" box="[264,390,845,868]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Arpedium" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="65" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="quadrum">
<emphasis id="B941EAE7FF89FF94FEFBFC96FE0CFC8D" box="[264,390,845,868]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="65">A. quadrum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by much smaller size, darker coloration especially of pronotum and elytra, less glossy, as well as more densely and distinctly pubescent forebody, reduced hind wings, shorter tibiae and tarsi, the much shorter antennae with less slender antennomeres, stouter maxillary palpi with relatively longer apical palpomeres, much smaller eyes, a distinctly more transverse and posteriorly more distinctly narrowed pronotum, distinctly finer and less well-defined puncturation of pronotum and elytra, much shorter and posteriorly more strongly dilated elytra, coarser and denser puncturation of the abdomen, and by the apically not distinctly dilated parameres of the aedeagus;
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B8A36F5FF89FF94FF34FBC6FCF3FB56" blockId="2.[151,1437,151,1423]" pageId="2" pageNumber="65">
From 
<taxonomicName id="4C354D76FF89FF94FEFEFBC6FE2AFBDD" authorityName="Coiffait" authorityYear="1982" box="[269,416,1053,1076]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Arpedium" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="65" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nepalicum">
<emphasis id="B941EAE7FF89FF94FEFEFBC6FE2AFBDD" box="[269,416,1053,1076]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="65">A. nepalicum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
[characters taken from description by 
<bibRefCitation id="EFA44B04FF89FF94FCACFBC6FB83FBDD" author="Coiffait, H." box="[863,1033,1053,1076]" pageId="2" pageNumber="65" pagination="21 - 179" refId="ref1985" refString="Coiffait, H. (1982) Contribution a la connaissance des Staphylinides de l'Himalaya (Nepal, Ladakh, Cachemire) (Insecta: Coleoptera: Staphylinidae). Senckenbergiana biologica, 62 (1981), 21 - 179." type="journal article" year="1982">Coiffait (1982)</bibRefCitation>
], whose male sexual characters are unknown, by distinctly larger size (
<taxonomicName id="4C354D76FF89FF94FDFEFB9BFD13FBBE" authorityName="Coiffait" authorityYear="1982" box="[525,665,1088,1111]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Arpedium" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="65" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nepalicum">
<emphasis id="B941EAE7FF89FF94FDFEFB9BFD13FBBE" box="[525,665,1088,1111]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="65">A. nepalicum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
: 
<quantity id="4CCD9B10FF89FF94FD54FB9BFD71FBBE" box="[679,763,1088,1111]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.5" pageId="2" pageNumber="65" unit="mm" value="2.5">2.5 mm</quantity>
), darker coloration (
<taxonomicName id="4C354D76FF89FF94FC20FB9BFBD5FBBE" authorityName="Coiffait" authorityYear="1982" box="[979,1119,1088,1111]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Arpedium" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="65" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nepalicum">
<emphasis id="B941EAE7FF89FF94FC20FB9BFBD5FBBE" box="[979,1119,1088,1111]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="65">A. nepalicum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
: whole body reddish yellow), more pronounced posterior angles of the pronotum (in 
<taxonomicName id="4C354D76FF89FF94FD2CFBB8FCE1FB93" authorityName="Coiffait" authorityYear="1982" box="[735,875,1123,1146]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Arpedium" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="65" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nepalicum">
<emphasis id="B941EAE7FF89FF94FD2CFBB8FCE1FB93" box="[735,875,1123,1146]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="65">A. nepalicum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
broadly rounded), reduced hind wings (in 
<taxonomicName id="4C354D76FF89FF94FAC0FBB8FF49FB75" authorityName="Coiffait" authorityYear="1982" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Arpedium" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="65" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nepalicum">
<emphasis id="B941EAE7FF89FF94FAC0FBB8FF49FB75" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="65">A. nepalicum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
almost reaching apex of abdomen), denser puncturation and the more pronounced microreticulation of the abdomen (in 
<taxonomicName id="4C354D76FF89FF94FF48FB73FECDFB56" authorityName="Coiffait" authorityYear="1982" box="[187,327,1192,1215]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Arpedium" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="65" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nepalicum">
<emphasis id="B941EAE7FF89FF94FF48FB73FECDFB56" box="[187,327,1192,1215]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="65">A. nepalicum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
with shallow transverse microsculpture and glossy);
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B8A36F5FF89FF94FF34FB11FBA4FAA0" blockId="2.[151,1437,151,1423]" pageId="2" pageNumber="65">
From the species currently attributed to 
<taxonomicName id="4C354D76FF89FF94FD9DFB10FD7FFB0B" authorityName="Reitter" authorityYear="1909" box="[622,757,1227,1250]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Eucnecosum" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="65" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B941EAE7FF89FF94FD9DFB10FD7FFB0B" box="[622,757,1227,1250]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="65">Eucnecosum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the absence of microsculpture on the head and pronotum, by the longer impressions in front of the ocelli, by the stouter maxillary palpus with a relatively longer apical palpomere, by the distinctly more transverse, less convex (cross-section), and posteriorly more distinctly narrowed pronotum, the coarser puncturation of the pronotum, and by the denser puncturation of the abdomen.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C32F657EFF89FF94FF34FA8FFA16FA16" pageId="2" pageNumber="65" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="8B8A36F5FF89FF94FF34FA8FFBD2FA66" blockId="2.[151,1437,151,1423]" pageId="2" pageNumber="65">
<emphasis id="B941EAE7FF89FF94FF34FA8FFD8CFA85" bold="true" box="[199,518,1364,1388]" inLineHeading="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="65" reason="1">Distribution and bionomics.</emphasis>
The 
<typeStatus id="548E8857FF89FF94FDCDFA8EFDE6FA85" box="[574,620,1365,1388]" pageId="2" pageNumber="65">type</typeStatus>
locality is situated in eastern 
<collectingCountry id="F3227665FF89FF94FC5FFA8EFBA3FA85" box="[940,1065,1365,1388]" name="Kyrgyzstan" pageId="2" pageNumber="65">Kyrgyzstan</collectingCountry>
, to the south of the Issyk-kul lake. The specimens were found under stones in stony grassland at an altitude of 
<quantity id="4CCD9B10FF89FF94FC4EFAA3FBDEFA66" box="[957,1108,1400,1423]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.775" metricValueMax="3.85" metricValueMin="3.7" pageId="2" pageNumber="65" unit="m" value="3775.0" valueMax="3850.0" valueMin="3700.0">3700–3850 m</quantity>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B8A36F5FF89FF94FB47FA19FA16FA16" blockId="2.[620,1436,1474,1535]" pageId="2" pageNumber="65">
VOLKER ASSING 
<emphasis id="B941EAE7FF89FF94FD9FFA31FA16FA16" box="[620,1436,1514,1535]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="65">
Gabelsbergerstr. 2, D-30163 Hannover, 
